http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Vijayawada/400-life-convicts-in-AP-set-to-walk-free/article14021274.ece

The Andhra Pradesh government has taken a decision to release 400 life convicts on a special remission of sentence on the eve of Republic Day.Their release will be however subject to two main conditions that they should appear before the probation officers/police stations concerned once in three months till the completion of unexpired portion of sentence and execute a personal bond of Rs. 50,000 each.It was a landmark gesture that the Cabinet has made at its meeting held here on Monday.Another significant decision was to introduce the budget for 2016-17 in the first week of March.